                            <comment id="17205142" author="reuvenlax" created="Wed, 30 Sep 2020 23:36:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;pr/12980 rolls back this PR.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Just a quick browse of that PR shows some possible problems. If a timer shows up in a bundle but is then deleted before it fires (i.e. in a processElement or in a different timer firing), then I believe this PR will cause us to leak the watermark hold.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note: that the behavior prior to this PR is that the timer will fire despite having been deleted, because it was already captured in the bundle. That behavior is also incorrect, so I think it should be high priority to fix the problems in that PR and resubmit it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17205837" author="robinyqiu" created="Thu, 1 Oct 2020 21:29:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is the PR ready to merge now? This is currently the only blocker for 2.25 release&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
